Preface

What?

R Markdown is an authoring format that enables easy creation of dynamic documents, presentations, and reports from R. It combines the core syntax of markdown (an easy-to-write plain text format) with embedded R code chunks that are run so their output can be included in the final document. R Markdown documents are fully reproducible (they can be automatically regenerated whenever underlying R code or data changes).

It happened everyday

  1. Data preparation
  2. Modeling
  3. Generating report
  4. Something wrong in your data
  5. Repeat 1 ~ 4

Why?

  1. Automate
    • Periodic documents
    • Adapted documents
    • Faster to implement
  2. Reproducible
    • Less errors
  3. Diferent formats
    • Html
    • Pdf
    • Presentations

how to start?

Installing R Markdown

  • RStudio — Install the latest version of RStudio

  • Other environments — Install the rmarkdown package.

Overview

  • YAML Metadata: YAML document options
  • Markdown: Article text
  • R Code Chunk: Executible R code

Rendering Output

  • RStudio: "Knit" command (Ctrl+Shift+K)
  • Command line: rmarkdown::render function
rmarkdown::render("input.Rmd")

Plain Code Blocks

  • Plain code blocks are displayed in a fixed-width font but not evaulated.

    ```
This text is displayed verbatim / preformatted
```

  • Specify the language of the block is avaliable

    ```r
x = rnorm(10)
```
